item.title: Demystifying Data Analysis: A Comprehensive Guide for Beginners
item.description: Understanding Data Types: We’ll begin by introducing readers to the different types of data encountered in data analysis, such as numerical, categorical, and ordinal data. We’ll explain the characteristics and significance of each data type, and provide examples to help readers better understand how to identify and work with different data types in their analyses. Data Collection Methods: In this section, we’ll explore various data collection methods, such as surveys, interviews, and observational studies.
